	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-29T04:41:01">Amara Mining plc is a junior gold mining company. The Company is engaged in acquisition, exploration, development and operation of gold mines and deposits in West Africa. The Company is developing the Yaoure Gold Project in Cote d'Ivoire and the Baomahun Gold Project in Sierra Leone. The Yaoure Gold Project is located in central Cote d'Ivoire, 40 kilometers from the political capital, Yamoussoukro. Baomahun is located in central Sierra Leone, approximately 180 kilometers east of the capital Freetown, the nearest town is the provincial capital Bo, located approximately 60 kilometers south of the Project. The project area consists of the Baomahun Mining Lease, which covers an area of approximately 59 square kilometers, and the adjoining Victoria Exploration Licence, which covers an area of over 77 square kilometers. Its subsidiaries include Amara Mining (Sierra Leone) Limited, Amara Mining (Burkina) Limited, Amara Mining (Cote d'Ivoire) Limited and Yaoure Mining SA, among others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-09-22T23:17:37">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, AMARA MINING PLC revenues was not reported. Net loss before extraordinary items decreased 28% to $2.8M. Lower net loss reflects General and administrative expenses decrease of 41% to $2.1M (expense), Finance costs decrease from $449K (expense) to $0K. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items remained flat at -$0.01.</Text>
